gomodel:SYNGO_4685  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 5 shows localisation of TNK2 (ACK1) to both axon terminals and dendritic spines using DAB immunolocalization in mouse hippocampus, neocortex and cerebellum. As the molecule does not contain a transmembrane domain or membrane binding motif, its localisation is cytosolic.. Experimental description: M&M:\" Adult mice (NMRI mice). \"\n\n\"incubated with rabbit antibody to Ack1/Pyk1 (1:100) for 2 days at 4°C.\" \"Two rabbit polyclonal antibodies (384 and 385) were generated using the GST fusion proteins corresponding to the proline-rich region (amino acids 502-1008) following standard protocols (Harlow, 1988).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
